  "prompt": "Which app should I use to locate lost or stolen phone even after a factory reset is performed? My phone is rooted.",
  "response": "If your phone is rooted, there are a few options that you can consider for tracking a lost or stolen device, even after a factory reset. However, it\u2019s important to note that most standard tracking solutions, such as Find My Device (Android) or Find My iPhone (iOS), will not work after a factory reset because they rely on the device\u2019s original account information, which is wiped during the reset.\n\n### Possible Solutions:\n\n1. **Cerberus Anti-Theft**:\n   - Cerberus is a comprehensive anti-theft app that works well with rooted devices. It provides several features, including remote tracking, taking pictures from the front and rear camera, and even recording ambient sounds. For it to work after a factory reset, you would have to ensure that it is well-configured beforehand.\n\n2. **Prey Anti Theft**:\n   - Prey is another good option that allows tracking of devices even after factory resets under certain conditions if it's set up properly beforehand. It provides features like geolocation, screenshot captures, and info about the network.\n\n3. **Google Maps Timeline**:\n   - If your location history was enabled in Google Maps before the device was lost, you may still be able to see your device's last known locations through your Google account.\n\n4. **Custom ROMs**:\n   - If you have experience with rooting and flashing Roms, consider installing a custom ROM that includes advanced tracking features, although this will vary widely depending on the specific ROM.\n\n### Important Considerations:\n- **Pre-Installation**: For any of the above tools to work after a factory reset, they generally need to be installed and configured before the device is lost.\n- **Privacy**: Always consider the privacy implications of installing tracking apps and ensure you comply with legal requirements regarding tracking devices.\n- **Security**: Make sure that you have strong security measures in place (like a password or PIN) to help prevent unauthorized access to the tracking software.\n\nIt's important to remember that security and privacy practices are crucial, and tracking should always be done ethically and legally.",
